  "text": "## AddressSanitizer Implementation Analysis\n\nAddressSanitizer (ASan) is implemented across both LLVM and GCC with distinct architectures:\n\n### LLVM/LLVM-Project Implementation\n\n**1. ASan Interceptors (compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_interceptors.cpp)**\n- Implements interception of standard library functions (malloc, free, pthread operations, string functions)\n- Uses INTERCEPTOR macros to wrap libc functions\n- Starts at line 311 with pthread_create and continues with numerous library function interceptors\n- This runtime component captures memory operations at the libc level\n\n**2. ASan Runtime Library (compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_rtl.cpp)**\n- Main file of the ASan run-time library (RTL)\n- Contains the critical `__asan_init()` function (line 678) that initializes ASan when the program starts\n- Initializes shadow memory, registers error handlers, and sets up the sanitizer runtime environment\n- Called during program initialization via module constructors\n\n**3. LLVM IR-Level Instrumentation Pass (llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp)**\n- `AddressSanitizerPass` class: The main modern pass implementation that orchestrates instrumentation\n- `AddressSanitizer` struct (line 776): Function-level sanitizer that instruments individual functions\n- `ModuleAddressSanitizer` class (line 930): Module-level sanitizer handling globals and initialization\n- Inserts memory access checks at the LLVM IR level before each load/store operation\n- The pass instruments shadow memory checks that run at program execution\n\n### GCC Implementation\n\n**4. ASan Instrumentation Implementation (gcc/asan.cc)**\n- `asan_instrument()` function (line 4430): Main entry point for ASan instrumentation pass\n- `pass_asan` class (line 4468): GIMPLE optimization pass that extends gimple_opt_pass\n- `pass_asan_O0` class (line 4511): Variant for unoptimized builds\n- These passes instrument GIMPLE IR to add runtime checks for memory operations\n- Both pass classes call `asan_instrument()` to perform the actual instrumentation\n\n**5. ASan Header Declarations (gcc/asan.h)**\n- Declares public API functions including:\n  - `asan_function_start()`: Called at function entry\n  - `asan_finish_file()`: Finalizes instrumentation metadata\n  - `asan_emit_stack_protection()`: Protects stack memory with red zones\n  - `asan_protect_global()`: Marks global variables for monitoring\n  - `asan_expand_check_ifn()`, `asan_expand_mark_ifn()`, `asan_expand_poison_ifn()`: Expand ASan-specific intrinsics\n\n### Instrumentation Flow\n\n**LLVM**: AddressSanitizerPass → AddressSanitizer (per-function) → ModuleAddressSanitizer (globals) → Inserts shadow memory checks at IR level\n\n**GCC**: pass_asan/pass_asan_O0 → asan_instrument() → Adds checks at GIMPLE level\n\nBoth implementations follow a similar pattern: instrument code to check if memory accesses are valid by consulting shadow memory before execution, with initialization code that sets up the shadow memory mapping and registers error handlers at program startup."
}

